<exercises>
    <exercise>
        <statement>
            <p>Suppose <m>T</m> is a linear map.
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        If <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k</m> are dependent, why are <m>T(v_1),\ldots,T(v_k)</m> dependent?
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k</m> are independent, need <m>T(v_1),\ldots,T(v_k)</m> be independent?
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If <m>T(v_1),\ldots,T(v_k)</m> are dependent, need <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k</m> be dependent?
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        If <m>T(v_1),\ldots,T(v_k)</m> are independent, why are <m>v_1,\ldots,v_k</m> are independent?
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
        </statement>
    </exercise>
</exercises>

